SUMMARY:Davis High School Presents Urinetown—The Musical!
DESCRIPTION:Urinetown: The Musical \nSet in a grim\, Gotham-like city ravaged by a 20-year drought\, Urinetown imagines a world where private toilets are outlawed. Citizens must pay to use public restrooms\, all controlled by a single\, corrupt corporation that profits off one of humanity’s most basic needs. When an unlikely hero decides he’s had enough\, a rebellion is born—one that challenges authority\, exposes hypocrisy\, and asks what freedom really costs. \nHilariously funny and touchingly human\, Urinetown reexamines the very notion of what a musical can be\, proving that even in the darkest circumstances\, revolution can begin with a laugh—or a pee. \nLocation\nBrunelle Theater @ 315 W 14th Street. \nPerformances\nFriday March 6\, Saturday March 7\, Friday March 13\, Saturday March 14 @7:00PM\nSunday March 8 and Sunday March 15 @2:00PM \nTickets\n$15 general admission\, $10 for DJUSD students\, and $5 on Sundays for DJUSD students. \nYou can buy your tickets online at https://sites.google.com/view/davishightheatre/home or at the door. We hope to see you there!
URL:https://thedirt.online/event/davis-high-school-presents-urinetown-the-musical/2026-03-08/
LOCATION:Richard Brunelle Performance Hall\, 315 W 14th Street\, Davis\, CA\, 95616\, United States
CATEGORIES:Stage & Dance
